`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- `createPortal(children, camera)` from `@react-three/fiber` renders Three.js children as children of the camera Object3D — this is the canonical R3F approach for camera-space rendering (weapon/tool view models) without per-frame matrix math
- `scene.clone(true)` in a `useMemo` is essential because `useGLTF` returns a cached scene — using the same scene object in multiple `<primitive>` calls would silently steal the object from its previous parent in the Three.js scene graph
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
